-- Hillary Clinton Pledges $10 Million U.S. Relief Aid to Flood-Hit Pakistan
-- Bill Austin
-- 2010-08-02T00:10:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/hillary-clinton-pledges-10-million-in-relief-aid-to-flood-hit-pakistan.html

          
          
             Secretary of State Hillary Clinton
pledged $10 million in emergency aid to Pakistan for relief
efforts following devastating floods in the countryâ€™s northwest.  
 The U.S. is rushing helicopters, boats, pre-fabricated
bridges, mobile water treatment units and food supplies to
affected areas, Clinton said in a statement yesterday.  
 As many as 3,000 people may have died in flash floods,
according to Edhi rescue service.  
          
          


  


        